description: BJP and DSS criticize Karnataka government for diverting Rs 13,435 crore from Scheduled Caste and Tribe funds to Congress’s guarantee schemes. SC-ST representatives claim this move undermines their rights as the funds are meant for community development, not populist measures. Government officials argue a significant portion of the beneficiaries are from SC-ST communities.
title: BJP slams Cong as Karnataka SC/ST funds diverted to ‘5 guarantees’

description: Canada's governing Liberals have elected former Bank of Canada governor Mark Carney as Prime Minister, amid a tariff conflict with the United States initiated by Donald Trump. Carney, who is highly regarded for his role during the 2008 financial crisis, has already taken a strong stance against Trump’s tariffs.
title: Canada's Liberals elect Mark Carney to replace PM Justin Trudeau

description: Vizianagaram MP K Appala Naidu has pledged Rs 50,000 for every third baby girl born in his constituency, aiming to support the raise in population and promote gender equality. Inspired by CM Chandrababu Naidu and influenced by women in his life, he announced the offer during Women's Day celebrations, emphasizing the importance of empowering women.
title: In 3rd child push, TDP MP offers women Rs 50k for a girl, cow & calf for a boy

description: CPM’s state conference unanimously re-elects M V Govindan as Kerala unit secretary, with no factional dissent. CM Pinarayi Vijayan defends proposals for accepting private capital for Kerala's development, adopted in the conference, emphasizing continuous LDF governance has improved conditions significantly.
title: Kerala CPM set to chart new path, eyes private participation for revival of loss-making PSUs

description: Maharashtra's Mahayuti government faces a tight budget balancing act between managing a soaring debt and fiscal deficit while maintaining welfare schemes. Despite expanding farmer aid, increasing the Ladki Bahin stipend seems unlikely. The state aims to reduce the fiscal deficit to 3% of GSDP, focusing on revenue growth despite global economic challenges.
title: Maha budget will seek to strike balance between fiscal prudence & welfare plans
'No power to fire people': US Senators on Elon Musk's role in Trump admins

description: Tamil Nadu chief minister M K Stalin has decided to send senior DMK leaders to meet with chief ministers and politicians from seven states to oppose the Centre's proposed population-based delimitation exercise. Stalin has also instructed DMK MPs to raise key issues including opposition to Hindi imposition and the National Education Policy during the Parliament session.
title: Stalin to enlist support of 7 states in delimitation fight
Who is Mark Carney? Canada’s new Liberal leader and next PM amid rising Trump trade war
2 kids drown, another feared dead in Madhya Pradesh
Hampi horror: 3rd suspect nabbed in Tamil Nadu
Madhav National Park in MP India’s 58th tiger reserve now
Maha cop lies to woman about special event, rapes her; held

description: Baptist Church of Mizoram (BCM) has urged married church members to have more children to counter falling birth rates and the influx of illegal immigrants, particularly Buddhist Chakmas from Bangladesh. The call to action highlights concerns that a declining population could adversely impact Mizo society, the state, and the church.
title: Mizoram church to members: Have more kids, ‘save religion’

description: The Uttarakhand high court has prevented police from taking coercive actions against journalist Sudhanshu Thapliyal, who was detained for a Facebook post criticizing the lack of arrests in a fatal accident case. Thapliyal stressed his duty to highlight injustices. Journalists and associations condemned his detention, calling for an impartial investigation into the arrest.
title: No action on scribe held for social media post, rules HC

description: A Rajasthan police constable, Bhagaram, has been arrested for allegedly raping a 27-year-old pregnant woman in a Jaipur hotel while her three-year-old son was in the room. He had enticed her by claiming to take her statement about her husband’s dispute, threatening her with her husband’s imprisonment if she resisted.
title: Rajasthan cop held for raping pregnant woman in hotel

description: Shiromani Akali Dal (SAD) issued show-cause notices to Bikram Singh Majithia and other members for public criticism of the SGPC's removal of two jathedars. SAD's Balwinder Singh Bhunder emphasized the importance of party discipline. The dissent has triggered internal conflicts and further scrutiny by the disciplinary committee, with potential actions pending their responses.
title: SAD raps ‘rebels’ as Majithia show of defiance sparks row

description: Communal clashes broke out in Mhow, near Indore, following India's ICC Champions Trophy victory celebrations. Violence erupted after stone-pelting during a procession, leading to arson and injuries. Police intervened with lathicharge and teargas, restoring order by midnight. Additional forces were deployed to control the situation.
title: Tension in MP town after communal clashes over India’s cricket victory

description: In Uttar Pradesh's Sitapur, three revenue officials and nine others were detained for questioning regarding the murder of journalist and RTI activist Raghvendra Bajpai. The investigation, which involves multiple teams, is exploring Bajpai's reports on alleged irregularities as potential motives for the crime. His wife has demanded severe punishment for the perpetrators and financial aid from the state.
title: 3 revenue officials among 12 held for scribe murder

description: US officials are challenging European regulations targeting American tech firms. FCC Chairman Brendan Carr criticized the EU's Digital Services Act. President Trump vowed retaliatory measures against countries imposing penalties on US tech companies. The administration is also opposing Europe's Digital Markets Act, which affects companies like Meta and Google.
title: Donald Trump unhappy with EU 'taxing' and 'troubling' American technology companies, says will defend them from 'foreign extortion'

description: A damaged MGL pipeline caused by unauthorized excavation in Andheri East led to a 40ft-high blaze, injuring three motorists and gutting multiple vehicles. The fire was contained after the gas supply was quickly disconnected. An FIR has been filed against the contractor and operator for negligence, with an inquiry report sought from the fire department and BMC.
title: Gas pipeline leak on road triggers 40ft-high blaze in Mumbai, 2 critical

description: In a significant move, the Supreme Court of India canceled the bail granted to two individuals involved in an impersonation case during a government job exam. The apex court emphasized the importance of maintaining integrity in public administration and highlighted the impact of such acts on societal faith in the system. The trial court's decision to deny bail was supported.
title: Impersonation in govt job exam serious crime, says SC; nixes bail

description: Defence Minister Rajnath Singh and IAF chief witnessed the handover of the first rear fuselage for the Tejas Mark-1A jet produced by the private sector to HAL, marking progress in India's self-reliance in defense. Despite delays, HAL aims to meet additional delivery commitments for the IAF starting from 2025-26 through partnerships with private Indian companies.
title: ‘Make in India’ boost as private company produces key Tejas component
Man steps out of BMW, pees on road; surrenders as clip goes viral

description: The Indian government condemned the vandalization of a Hindu temple by Khalistan separatists in California as despicable. They urged local law enforcement to take stringent action and ensure the security of places of worship. The incident, involving anti-Hindu messages, occurred ahead of the Khalistan referendum in Los Angeles, alarming the local Hindu community and prompting united resistance against hate.
title: Pro-Khalistan group defaces US temple, India calls it ‘despicable’
To fight pollution, K’taka bans sale of soaps, shampoos near waterbodies
Trump says Zelenskyy took money from US 'like candy from a baby under Biden'

description: Jharkhand police's investigation into the killing of NTPC deputy general manager Kumar Gaurav has led to questioning over a dozen people. Officials are exploring the possibility that Gaurav was mistaken for another officer. Gaurav was shot dead in a suspected attack linked to the coal mining mafia, while he was on his way to work in Hazaribag.
title: Was NTPC DGM mistakenly killed? Cops quiz over a dozen

description: India's cricket team, led by Rohit Sharma, has dominated international cricket over the past two years, securing victories in the 2024 T20 World Cup and the 2025 ICC Champions Trophy, both with unbeaten records. Despite losing the 2023 ICC ODI World Cup final to Australia, their consistent performance in global tournaments highlights their supremacy in the sport.
title: 23-1 win-loss record! India's dominant run in last three ICC tournaments
Meghan Markle under fire after fans spot Lilibet without safety vest in boat photo

description: Elon Musk has denied claims that Starlink would turn off its terminals in Ukraine, emphasizing its crucial role in maintaining Ukrainian communication lines. Musk asserted that despite disagreements over Ukraine policy, Starlink support will continue, highlighting its significance against Russian communication jamming efforts.
title: Musk on Starlink turning off terminals in Ukraine: To be extremely clear ...

description: India clinched their third ICC Champions Trophy with a thrilling four-wicket victory over New Zealand in Dubai. Key performances from captain Rohit Sharma, Shreyas Iyer, and spinners Varun Chakravarthy and Kuldeep Yadav were crucial in this success. Congratulations poured in from President Draupadi Murmu, PM Narendra Modi, and Defence Minister Rajnath Singh, celebrating the historic win.
title: Prez Murmu, PM Modi, Rajnath Singh hail India's Champions Trophy win

description: Microsoft CEO Satya Nadella congratulated the Indian cricket team and Captain Rohit Sharma for their Champions Trophy 2025 win against New Zealand. Nadella, a known cricket enthusiast, especially praised Rohit Sharma and Virat Kohli’s performances. His congratulatory post on X garnered immense engagement. Nadella’s passion for cricket continues to be expressed through public platforms and events.
title: Satya Nadella congratulates team India on winning Champions Trophy

description: Union minister Jitendra Singh condemned the killing of three family members in Jammu and Kashmir’s Kathua district as a terrorist attack. Their bodies were discovered after an extensive search. Lt governor Manoj Sinha ordered an investigation, sparking protests in Billawer town. If confirmed, it would be the deadliest civilian strike in Jammu since 2024.
title: Terrorists killed 3 missing civilians in J&K's Kathua: Union minister

description: India secured their third Champions Trophy title, defeating New Zealand by four wickets in Dubai. Rohit Sharma’s pivotal 76-run performance and KL Rahul's unbeaten 34 were crucial for India, who remained undefeated throughout the tournament. This win establishes India as the most successful team in Champions Trophy history. With this victory, India further cemented their status as the most successful team in Champions Trophy history, winning the prestigious tournament without a single defeat.
title: 'Koi future plan hai nahi': Rohit Sharma

description: India ended their 12-year ICC ODI title drought by defeating New Zealand by four wickets to win their third ICC Champions Trophy. India chased down New Zealand’s 252-run target, with Rohit Sharma scoring 76 and contributions from KL Rahul, Hardik Pandya, and Ravindra Jadeja ensuring the win. Varun Chakaravarthy and Kuldeep Yadav were key with the ball.
title: When you leave, you want to leave the team in a better place: Virat Kohli
Budget session: Adjournments, chaos likely amid Centre vs oppn over key issues

description: In a post-match celebration, Virat Kohli and Rohit Sharma performed an impromptu Dandiya dance with the match stumps after India's thrilling four-wicket victory over New Zealand in the 2025 Champions Trophy final. India chased down 252, led by Rohit Sharma's 76, and secured their third Champions Trophy title, highlighting their dominance in white-ball cricket.
title: Dandiya with stumps! Virat, Rohit light up celebration - Watch
'Exceptional result': PM Modi congratulates Team India on Champions Trophy win

description: A 24-year-old man, Asif Raza, was arrested for beheading his girlfriend after she pressured him to marry her. Police discovered the headless body near Jagannathpur village and linked Raza to the crime. He confessed, stating he was influenced by the Telugu film Salaar.
title: Girlfriend asks UP man for marriage, he beheads her

description: Countries are tightening immigration rules while offering investment-based residency through golden visa programmes. These visas provide affluent individuals residency in exchange for financial investments, offering enhanced mobility, security, and access to employment, education, and healthcare within the host country.
title: Golden visa programmes for Indians: Check minimum capital required
'Hats off to Rohit Sharma': Shama Mohamad hails India win in Champions Trophy

description: India emerged victorious in the 2025 Champions Trophy final, defeating New Zealand by successfully chasing 252 runs with an over to spare at the Dubai International Stadium. Captain Rohit Sharma's initial aggressive performance, backed by crucial contributions from Shreyas Iyer and KL Rahul, sealed the memorable win.
title: India's icy nerves, fiery spirit: Men in Blue lift ICC Champions Trophy title
Pittsburgh student Sudiksha Konanki vanishes while 'walking on beach', 'last seen in bikini'

description: India triumphed over New Zealand by four wickets to win the ICC Champions Trophy 2025, ending their 12-year wait for an ODI title. Rohit Sharma led the chase with a composed 76, supported by crucial contributions from Shreyas Iyer and Axar Patel. India's spinners played a key role, restricting New Zealand to 251/7.
title: Team India ends long ICC ODI title drought after winning Champions Trophy

description: India clinched their third ICC Champions Trophy title by defeating New Zealand in the final at Dubai, marking their dominance in white-ball cricket. The victory follows their previous wins in 2002 and 2013, adding another prestigious ICC trophy to their collection. This triumph also highlights their perfect campaign and redemption after being runners-up in 2017.
title: Where India stand on the list of Champions Trophy winners
With eyes on Bihar polls, Amit Shah announces grand Sita temple

description: Canada is poised to welcome a new prime minister as the Liberal Party selects a successor to Justin Trudeau, who resigned in January. The leadership race is led by former Bank of Canada governor Mark Carney, with results set to be announced Sunday.
title: Canada’s next Prime Minister: The race, the rules, and what’s next

description: The Los Angeles Lakers have produced numerous basketball legends who have successfully transitioned their on-court fame into substantial financial empires. From Magic Johnson to LeBron James, these players have built wealth through smart investments, endorsements, and business ventures, showcasing that their legacies extend far beyond their athletic achievements.
title: Richest Los Angeles Lakers players of all time: LeBron James, Magic Johnson and more
'Roads full of corpses': Alawites narrate ordeal of mass killings in Syria

description: President Donald Trump and Vice President JD Vance fought with Zelenskyy on television as Vance accused Zelenskyy of not being grateful enough for all that te US has been doing to resolve the war. After Zelenskyy's humiliation, many European leaders supported Zelenskyy. Zelenskyy's meeting with King Charles was scheduled at the same time. And to 'hurt' Trump some more, outgoing Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau too met King Charles.
title: Trump 'sulking' as King Charles met Zelenskyy: 'President now feels less special'
US-Hamas discuss release of hostages, envoy says deal possible 'within weeks'

description: India skipper Rohit Sharma led from the front in the ICC Champions Trophy final, smashing a rapid 41-ball half-century. His innings featured five boundaries and three sixes, setting up India’s chase against New Zealand. Along with Shubman Gill, Rohit established a solid foundation, making a significant impact on India's pursuit of 252 runs.
title: CT Final: Rohit Sharma slams fifty to lead from the front in India's run chase

description: Suniel Shetty joyfully discussed daughter Athiya Shetty’s pregnancy, while Govinda admitted regret over rejecting a Rs 100 crore project. Fans urged Anushka Sharma to motivate Virat Kohli for a crucial match. Dhanashree Verma’s cryptic post amid divorce rumors sparked curiosity, and Kiran Rao shared her parents' initial concerns about her marriage to Aamir Khan.
title: From Suniel Shetty on Athiya’s pregnancy to Govinda on slapping himself: Top 5 news
Indefinite strike brings Manipur to standstill on day 2 of 'free movement' directive
'No offer, don't talk nonsense': Why Tejashwi got angry on Nitish question

description: Glenn Phillips' stunning one-handed catch dismissed Shubman Gill in the Champions Trophy 2025 final, reviving New Zealand’s hopes as they defended 251 runs against India. Earlier, India's spinners, led by Kuldeep Yadav and Varun Chakaravarthy, stifled New Zealand's scoring. Phillips' fielding brilliance might be remembered as the defining moment in this tense match.
title: Phillips takes one-handed blinder to dismiss Gill - Watch

description: Daryl Mitchell and Michael Bracewell led New Zealand to 251/7 in the ICC Champions Trophy final against India in Dubai. Despite quick wickets from India’s Varun Chakaravarthy and Kuldeep Yadav, Mitchell's 63 and Bracewell’s unbeaten 53 boosted New Zealand. India face a challenging chase under the final's pressure and Dubai’s slow pitch conditions.
title: New Zealand set a challenging target for India in Champions Trophy final

description: India's spin quartet, led by Kuldeep Yadav, has been instrumental in their Champions Trophy success at the Dubai International Stadium. Despite diverse pitch conditions, the spinners' skill and captain Rohit Sharma's strategic rotation have stifled opponents. Kuldeep's performance against New Zealand highlighted his growing rhythm and effectiveness in crucial phases of the tournament.
title: Spin, strangle, conquer: India's quartet chokes New Zealand in CT final

description: A man was shot by the US Secret Service near the White House on Sunday, while President Trump was in Florida. The shooting is under investigation by the Metropolitan Police Department. The man was reportedly suicidal, and the incident involved an armed confrontation with law enforcement. No other injuries were reported.
title: US Secret Service shoots armed man near White House while Trump out of town
'Was instructed to not speak against...': Digvijaya Singh on Rahul Gandhi's statement

description: Elon Musk has accused billionaires George Soros and Reid Hoffman of funding recent protests at Tesla showrooms. He alleged five ActBlue-funded groups are responsible for the demonstrations, criticizing the financiers and ActBlue amidst ongoing investigation concerns and senior official resignations.
title: Elon Musk makes a 'big revelation' on people behind Tesla protests

description: Four labourers died from suffocation while cleaning a water tank at a construction site in Mumbai. A fifth worker survived and is receiving treatment. The police have begun investigating possible safety protocol lapses and the conditions that led to the fatal incident.
title: Four labourers suffocate to death while cleaning water tank in Mumbai
'His White House outfit wasn't casual wear': Why Zelenskyy doesn't wear suit

description: Jammu and Kashmir lieutenant governor Manoj Sinha promised justice and accountability after three civilians were killed in Kathua district. A thorough and transparent investigation has been ordered. Union minister Jitendra Singh suspected terrorist involvement, while protests and shutdowns occurred in Billawar in response to the killings.
title: J&K LG orders 'thorough and transparent probe' into Kathua killings
'Body stuck in machine': One body recovered from collapsed Telangana tunnel

description: China defended its increased defense spending, citing challenges in safeguarding national sovereignty and territorial integrity. The funds will enhance new combat capabilities and strengthen reconnaissance, early warning, joint strikes, and logistics support. With a $249 billion budget for 2023, China aims to improve military training under combat conditions and deepen defense reforms.
title: China justifies $245 billion defense budget, cites territorial integrity challenges

description: DMK MPs resolve to address delimitation and 'Hindi-imposition' issues in the upcoming parliamentary session. Led by CM MK Stalin, they plan to garner support from southern and other affected states to ensure no loss of Lok Sabha seats for Tamil Nadu post-delimitation.
title: DMK gears up for Parliament session, seeks allies to oppose delimitation

description: New Zealand's Matt Henry will miss the 2025 ICC Champions Trophy final against India due to a shoulder injury, replaced by Nathan Smith. Henry's standout performance throughout the tournament and history against India marks a significant loss for New Zealand. Indian captain Rohit Sharma set a record by losing his 12th consecutive toss, equaling Brian Lara's record.
title: Matt Henry breaks down after missing out on the Champions Trophy final

description: Bihar police have been directed to crackdown on the public playing of obscene Bhojpuri songs to safeguard women's dignity and social morals. Additionally, an advisory has been issued to police personnel for exercising caution and ensuring adequate backup during raids, due to an attack on officers by the liquor mafia.
title: Bihar police to crack down on double-meaning Bhojpuri songs in public

description: Bollywood has always been synonymous with glitz, glamour, and exclusivity. Beyond dazzling premieres, red carpet events, and award functions, a world of high-profile parties exists where networking is said to be just as crucial as talent. For decades, these Page 3 parties have served as breeding grounds for deals, friendships, and career launches. But how vital are these gatherings for making it in the industry? Can an outsider truly become an insider just by attending them? Or is it a carefully curated illusion, where connections matter more than credentials?
title: Bollywood, networking, and the Page 3 party circuit: How it works

description: Gaurav Ahuja was arrested by Pune city police for public misconduct at Yerwada junction. Under the influence of alcohol, he stopped his BMW and urinated in public view, leading to widespread outrage after a video of the incident went viral. Authorities have registered a case under multiple legal provisions and are currently searching for another individual involved.
title: 'Drunk' man who urinated on public road in Pune, arrested from Karad

description: Uttar Pradesh's Kunda MLA, Raghuraj Pratap Singh, also known as Raja Bhaiya, faces allegations from his wife, Bhanvi Singh, of years of physical and mental abuse. She accuses him and her in-laws of harassment, fearing for her life. Despite previous complaints, she took legal action after continued mistreatment. An FIR has been filed and investigation is underway.
title: FIR against UP MLA Raja Bhaiya: Wife alleges years of physical and mental abuse

description: The Hindu Mahasabha president condemned the vandalism of a Hindu temple in California, claiming local government protection. He called on the Trump administration to ensure the safety of Hindus. The Indian ministry of external affairs also urged stringent actions against those responsible and demanded adequate security for places of worship.
title: Hindu Mahasabha condemns temple vandalism in US, urges action from Trump

description: ​Senior FBI officials are not allowed to bring cell phones to their offices. A secured landline is already there on the desks of many FBI officials that can connect them to the White House, the CIA and other national security agencies. ​​But Kash Patel asked for a secured line direct to President Donald Trump both from his office and home, the Wall Street Journal reported.
title: Kash Patel asked how to get a direct phone line to Trump from home

description: India lost the toss for the 15th consecutive time in ODIs, this time in the 2025 ICC Champions Trophy final against New Zealand. Despite this streak, India remains unbeaten in the tournament and will play the final with an unchanged team, while New Zealand faces a setback with pacer Matt Henry's injury.
title: Memes flood internet as India lose 15th consecutive ODI toss

description: The Central Pollution Control Board's recent report has declared the water quality in Maha Kumbh as 'fit for bathing', following an earlier report that identified high faecal bacteria levels. The new findings emphasize data variability and the expert committee's analysis underscoring that water quality can vary significantly due to multiple factors.
title: New CPCB report says Kumbh water fit for bathing; cites 'variability in data'
PM Modi checks on VP Dhankhar at AIIMS, wishes him ‘speedy recovery’

description: On International Women's Day, the Taliban asserted their commitment to Afghan women's rights, claiming their protection and dignity are ensured. The statement clashes with the UN's ongoing criticism of severe restrictions on women since 2021, including bans on education, employment, and public appearances.
title: Taliban claim women's rights are protected, UN decries bans

description: India's Kuldeep Yadav turned the game around in the ICC Champions Trophy final by taking two crucial wickets after New Zealand's strong start. Following Rachin Ravindra and Will Young's 57-run opening stand, Kuldeep dismissed Ravindra and Kane Williamson, reducing New Zealand from 69/1 to 75/3. This pivotal moment shifted momentum in India's favour.
title: Watch: Kuldeep Yadav puts India on top with twin strikes in CT final

description: Elon Musk responded to criticisms of favouring Russia by claiming that he previously challenged Vladimir Putin to combat over Ukraine. Musk also pointed out that his Starlink system is critical for Ukraine's military. He called for sanctions on Ukrainian oligarchs and urged for an immediate ceasefire to end the conflict.
title: 'Challenged Putin to combat, supported Ukraine with Starlink': Elon Musk

description: A Florida couple is accused of kidnapping, killing, and dismembering 16-year-old Miranda Corsette. Authorities say the girl met Steven Gress via social media before being lured to his home. Evidence suggests she was killed and dismembered between 20 and 24 February. Gress and his partner Michelle Brandes are currently in custody with further charges expected.
title: Florida teen allegedly kidnapped, killed and dismembered by couple she met online

description: Mitchell Santner's New Zealand won the toss and opted to bat against India in the ICC Champions Trophy 2025 final at Dubai International Stadium. New Zealand's Matt Henry is out due to a shoulder injury, with Nathan Smith replacing him. India remains unchanged with their winning combination after defeating Australia.
title: IND vs NZ Final: New Zealand suffer big blow against unchanged India

description: Apple has indefinitely postponed promised AI updates to Siri due to flaws discovered by top executives. Initially scheduled for April's iOS 18.4 update, these features will now arrive "in the coming year." Significant bugs have hindered progress, leading to possible delays until next year, while competitors like Amazon forge ahead with their AI initiatives.
title: This Apple product 'didn’t work properly,' admits Craig Federighi

description: Two men were arrested for the rape of an Israeli tourist and her host, as well as the murder of an Odia tourist near Sanapur Lake, Koppal. The incident occurred on March 6, when the attackers demanded money and escalated to violence after the tourists refused. Another suspect is still absconding.
title: Dragged, drowned, assaulted: A night of music silenced by sounds of horror

description: The indefinite shutdown by Kuki-Zo groups in Manipur's Kangpokpi district continues to disrupt daily life, following confrontations with security forces over unrestricted movement directives. One protester died, and over 40 were injured, including security personnel. Authorities have intensified security and implemented vehicle patrols along NH-2 to maintain order.
title: Manipur: Uneasy calm in Kangpokpi district

description: Virat Kohli has an opportunity to become the leading run scorer in Champions Trophy history if he scores 46 runs in the final against New Zealand. Kohli, with 746 runs, is close to surpassing Chris Gayle's 791 runs. He also aims to overtake Kumar Sangakkara in ODIs and set records against New Zealand.
title: Records Kohli could break in Champions Trophy final

description: Robert Maudsley, a notorious serial killer in Britain, has started a hunger strike because prison authorities took away his PlayStation, TV, and books. He has spent nearly five decades in prison. His violent rampage led authorities to place him in extreme solitary confinement, inside a glass-walled cell built specifically to contain him.
title: Serial cannibal refuses to eat after prison authority seize play station

description: At Mumbai's Borivali railway station, a vigilant railway security personnel rescued a woman who lost her balance and fell while attempting to alight from a moving train. The Ministry of Railways urged commuters not to board or alight from moving trains by sharing a video of the incident on social media. Further details are awaited.
title: Watch: Railway security rescues woman dragged by moving train in Mumbai

description: A young woman in Rajasthan's Alwar was violently attacked by stray dogs, as recorded on CCTV. Another incident in Uttar Pradesh saw a six-year-old girl fatally mauled by a pack of dogs. Both incidents highlight the increasing threat of stray dog attacks, leading to injuries and fatalities.
title: Woman attacked by pack of stray dogs in Rajasthan

description: British actor Paapa Essiedu's casting as Severus Snape in the new Harry Potter TV series has sparked debate among fans. Some applaud his talent while others criticize the deviation from the book's description. Adam Driver is suggested as a closer match to Alan Rickman's portrayal. The series is expected to premiere in 2027 after being delayed.
title: Paapa Essiedu cast as Severus Snape in Harry Potter series in the docks

description: The ICC Champions Trophy 2025 final in Dubai has a reserve day in case the game remains unfinished on the schedule day. If play is interrupted, it resumes from the same point on the reserve day. A minimum of 25 overs per team is required to declare a result. If that is not possible on both the days, the teams will share the trophy.
title: Champions Trophy Final: In case of no result, winner will be...

description: President Trump denied reports of a clash between Elon Musk and Marco Rubio during a White House meeting on cost-cutting measures, calling it fake news. Tensions reportedly grew as Musk criticized Rubio's efforts, leading Trump to announce a more measured approach to cuts and limit Musk's influence.
title: 'Great relationship’: Trump dismisses reports of Musk-Rubio clash

description: The US Justice Department continues to push for Google to sell its Chrome browser, reinforcing its stance against the tech giant's monopoly in online search. The government argues for divesting Chrome and stopping paid agreements with Apple and other entities. Google plans to appeal, labeling the proposal as harmful and interventionist. Court arguments are set for April.
title: United States to Google: Sell Google Chrome to ….

description: The Ministry of External Affairs have condemned the vandalism of the BAPS Shri Swaminarayan Mandir in Chino Hills, California. BAPS public affairs vowed to resist hate and ensure peace. The Coalition of Hindus of North America linked the incident to Hinduphobia, drawing attention to similar attacks. Law enforcement is urged to take stringent action and ensure temple security.
title: 'Despicable acts': MEA condemns vandalism at Hindu Temple in California

description: NASA's James Webb Space Telescope captured stunning images of the developing star system Lynds 483, revealing intricate gas and dust structures from protostars. These observations offer valuable insights into star formation. The dynamic interactions of ejected materials in various hues highlight different densities, contributing to our understanding of stellar evolution. Future observations aim to explore the star formation dynamics further.
title: NASA's James Webb Space Telescope captures breathtaking view of star formation

description: The Trump administration has revoked the student visa of a Chinese scholar, Liu Lijun, for her involvement in pro-Palestinian rallies at UCLA. This move follows a broader crackdown on campus activism, targeting international students supporting pro-Palestinian causes amid rising concerns about antisemitism.
title: Warning shot over political activism by foreign students on US campuses

description: India and New Zealand will clash in the ICC Champions Trophy final in Dubai on Sunday. India, unbeaten in four matches, seek one last push for the title with batters like Shubman Gill and Virat Kohli leading the charge. New Zealand, having lost only once, face uncertainty over key bowler Matt Henry's fitness but remain upbeat about their chances.
title: 'Let's go and get this one' - Gill ahead of CT final

description: Congress leader Pawan Khera criticised PM Modi and the central government, after the US claiming that India reduced tariffs, claiming pressure from Donald Trump. Khera raised concerns about transparency and questions the government's negotiations. Meanwhile, reports indicated that PM Modi and Trump have agreed to advance a Bilateral Trade Agreement to improve market access and reduce trade barriers.
title: 'Pressure from Trump?' Cong questions centre over US claim on tariff cut
Vice president Jagdeep Dhankhar admitted to AIIMS

description: Team India is set to compete for their third ICC Champions Trophy title against New Zealand in Dubai on Sunday. Both teams, having faced recent disappointments in finals, are eager for glory. Key players like Rohit Sharma and Kane Williamson could potentially conclude their ODI careers. India's dominant journey and strong spin attack fuel high expectations in this finale.
title: Champions Trophy final: Clinical India wary of old bugbear New Zealand

description: Vicky Kaushal's historical drama Chhaava, directed by Laxman Utekar, surpassed the Rs 500 crore mark at the Indian box office in just 23 days. The film's strong performance, particularly in Maharashtra, led to impressive weekend growth and made it Vicky's highest-earning film. It also sparked a treasure hunt around Asirgarh fort in Madhya Pradesh.
title: Chhaava box office collection: Vicky Kaushal starrer hits Rs 500 crore mark

description: A visually impaired man was arrested at Bengaluru's Kempegowda International Airport for smuggling 3.4 crore worth of gold from Dubai. Customs officials intercepted the passenger, discovering 3,995.22 grams of gold hidden under his shirt. His arrest followed the detention of Kannada actress Ranya Rao, who was found with 14.2 kg of gold valued at Rs 12.56 crore.
title: Day after Ranya Rao arrest, visually impaired man caught for smuggling gold from Dubai

description: President Trump questioned the legitimacy of the US-Canada border treaty and suggested revising it in a call with PM Trudeau. He expressed frustration over trade issues such as Canada's protected dairy sector. Trudeau dismissed Trump's justification and accused him of economic weakening attempts.
title: Donald Trump wants to revisit US-Canada border treaty: Report

description: 18-year-old Pranav Venkatesh clinched the World Junior Chess Championship with unique preparation methods, including playing cricket in hotel rooms with his coach, GM Shyam Sundar. Pranav balanced his rapid blitz skills with the patience needed for classical chess, leading to his triumph in Montenegro, a title once held by Viswanathan Anand.
title: From hotel room cricket to world junior champion: Pranav's story

description: Nasa has postponed the launch of its SPHEREx and PUNCH missions scheduled on a SpaceX Falcon 9 rocket from California. The delay allows for further rocket checkouts. SPHEREx will scan the sky in infrared light to study galaxies and cosmic history, while PUNCH will investigate the sun's outer atmosphere and solar wind to improve space weather predictions.
title: Nasa postpones launch of two major space missions: SPHEREx and PUNCH

description: More than 80 Afghan women studying in Oman face imminent deportation after the Trump administration cut funding for their USAID scholarships. These women, barred from higher education by the Taliban, had fled Afghanistan seeking safety. They fear severe repercussions upon return, including forced marriage and targeted violence. They urgently seek international intervention for protection and financial assistance.
title: US aid cut leave 80 Afghan women stranded in Oman

description: A man climbed Big Ben’s Elizabeth Tower waving a Palestinian flag and shouting "Free Palestine." He spent 16 hours on the structure before being arrested by police. Authorities worked with emergency crews to safely negotiate the situation, leading to road closures and canceled parliamentary tours.
title: Watch: Man climbs Big Ben tower, waves Palestinian flag before arrest

description: Vice President JD Vance was confronted by pro-Ukraine protesters while walking with his three-year-old daughter in Cincinnati, leading to his daughter becoming anxious and scared. Vance engaged in a conversation with the protesters, who mostly agreed to leave them alone. The incident follows Vance's controversial involvement in a heated Oval Office meeting between Trump and Ukrainian President Zelensky.
title: Watch: Pro-Ukraine protesters confront JD Vance, family in Cincinnati

description: The iconic BAPS Hindu Temple in Chino Hills, California, faced vandalism with discriminatory messages, urging the Hindu community to stay united against hatred. The Coalition of Hindus of North America highlighted previous similar incidents and emphasized ongoing concerns about anti-Hindu sentiments.
title: BAPS Hindu Temple in California's Chino Hills vandalised

description: More than 1,000 people have died in Syria following intense clashes between security forces and Assad loyalists. The violence, which erupted after an insurgent-led government took power, has targeted Alawites and caused devastating retribution killings.
title: Clashes, ‘revenge’ killings leave over 1,000 dead in Syria: All you need to know

description: Luis Pena, former UFC fighter, faced multiple arrests for domestic violence in 2021, leading to his contract termination with UFC. Despite pleading not guilty, charges against him were dismissed in 2023 and 2022. UFC acknowledged his mental health struggles but decided to end his promotional agreement. Pena then joined ACA and continues his career in boxing.
title: UFC once terminated Luis Pena after two domestic violence arrests

description: India face New Zealand in the Champions Trophy final in Dubai on Sunday, with the Kiwis having defeated India in their previous two meetings in the final of an ICC tournament. Rohit Sharma and Virat Kohli aim for their fourth ICC title, but Akaash Chopra warns of New Zealand's process-driven approach and their ability to present stiff challenges.
title: CT Final: 'Process-driven' NZ a serious threat to India's pedigree

description: Ben Affleck feels happier since finalizing his divorce from Jennifer Lopez two months ago. They remain in touch for their children's school matters but maintain some distance. Affleck and his ex-wife Jennifer Garner were seen enjoying time together at their son Samuel's birthday celebration.
title: Ben Affleck ‘happier than in years’ amid divorce from Jennifer Lopez
GST rates set to drop: FM Nirmala Sitharaman

description: Gaurav Ahuja was arrested after being caught urinating in public and flashing morning walkers in Pune. Social activist Vijay Kumbhar shared the video, which led to public outrage. Ahuja later surrendered to the Karad city police. An FIR has been registered against him and his friend Bhagyash Prakash Oswal under various sections of the law.
title: Drunk Pune man steps out of BMW, pees in public, flashes passersby

description: Villagers in Burhanpur, MP, driven by rumours and recent movie influence, commenced digging near Asirgarh Fort in hopes of finding Mughal-era gold. The authorities intervened amidst growing chaos and have cordoned off the area, suspecting illegal excavation activities. Archaeological experts are set to evaluate the site.
title: Digging frenzy for ‘buried Mughal treasure’ around Asirgarh Fort in MP

description: Lajar Masih, a BKI terrorist arrested for planning blasts at Mahakumbh, revealed his involvement with Pakistan's ISI and drug trade operations. Radicalized via social media, Masih smuggled arms into India using drones and attacked police outposts in Punjab. His connections include terrorists in Germany, the US, and Qatar, as well as a local drug mafia.
title: 'Kumbh blast plotter lured with promise of better life abroad, ISI pulled the strings'

description: New Zealand are focusing on countering India's spin attack ahead of their ICC Champions Trophy final in Dubai. Preparation includes specific strategies against Indian left-arm spinners Kuldeep, Jadeja and Axar, with support from net bowlers to simulate match conditions. New Zealand batters aim to improve their performance against spin to challenge India.
title: CT Final: Unexpected source reveals NZ's plans for India

description: In Sidhi district, MP, a man killed his wife in a fit of anger and later died by suicide. The shock led his grieving grandfather to immolate himself on the pyre of his grandson and daughter-in-law. Police have registered cases of unnatural death and murder.
title: 65-year-old dies by suicide on grandson’s funeral pyre in Madhya Pradesh

description: Six MBBS doctors at Government Medical College, Bhavnagar kidnapped and assaulted three interns over an offending Instagram post. Police registered two FIRs, charging them with various offences. The college's anti-ragging committee held an urgent meeting and suspended four of the accused.
title: Ragging horror in Gujarat: MBBS interns assaulted over Instagram post

description: Rohini Khadse, NCP state women's wing president, has appealed to President Droupadi Murmu, asking for permission for women to commit one murder. She expressed concerns about women's safety and criticized the government's inaction. Khadse's request aims to highlight the need for stringent laws and societal change to protect women from harassment and violence.
title: ‘Allow women to commit one murder’: NCP (SP) leader to President Murmu
